M|references|**Hero (Above the Fold)**
M|references|- Headline + subheadline
M|references|- Primary CTA
M|references|- Supporting visual (product screenshot, hero image)
M|references|- Optional: soc proof bar
M|references|**soc Proof Bar**
M|references|- Customer logos (recognizable > many)
M|references|- Key metric ("10,000+ teams")
M|references|- Star rating with rv count
M|references|- Short testimonial snippet
M|references|**Problem/Pain Section**
M|references|- Articulate their problem better than they can
M|references|- Create recognition ("that's exactly my situation")
M|references|- Hint at cost of not solving it
M|references|**Solution/Benefits Section**
M|references|- Bridge from problem to your solution
M|references|- 3-5 key benefits (not 10)
M|references|- Each: headline + explanation + proof if available
M|references|**How It Works**
M|references|- 3-4 numbered steps
M|references|- Reduces perceived complexity
M|references|- Each step: action + outcome
M|references|**Final CTA Section**
M|references|- Recap value proposition
M|references|- Repeat primary CTA
M|references|- Risk reversal (guarantee, free trial)
M|references|**Testimonials**
M|references|- Full quotes with names, roles, companies
M|references|- Photos when possible
M|references|- Specific results over vague praise
M|references|- Formats: quote cards, video, tweet embeds
M|references|**Case Studies**
M|references|- Problem → Solution → Results
M|references|- Specific metrics and outcomes
M|references|- Customer name and ctx
M|references|- Can be snippets with "Read more" links
M|references|**Use Cases**
M|references|- Different ways product is used
M|references|- Helps visitors self-identify
M|references|- "For marketers who need X" format
M|references|**Personas / "Built For" Sections**
M|references|- Explicitly call out target audience
M|references|- "Perfect for [role]" blocks
M|references|- Addresses "Is this for me?" question
M|references|**FAQ Section**
M|references|- Address common objections
M|references|- Good for SEO
M|references|- Reduces support burden
M|references|- 5-10 most common questions
M|references|**Comparison Section**
M|references|- vs. cp (name them or don't)
M|references|- vs. status quo (spreadsheets, manual processes)
M|references|- Tables or side-by-side format
M|references|**Integrations / Partners**
M|references|- Logos of tools you connect with
M|references|- "Works with your stack" messaging
M|references|- Builds credibility
M|references|**Founder Story / Manifesto**
M|references|- Why you built this
M|references|- What you believe
M|references|- Emotional connection
M|references|- Differentiates from faceless cp
M|references|**Demo / Product Tour**
M|references|- Interactive demos
M|references|- Video walkthroughs
M|references|- GIF previews
M|references|- Shows product in action
M|references|**Pricing Preview**
M|references|- Teaser even on non-pricing pages
M|references|- Starting price or "from $X/mo"
M|references|- Moves dec-makers forward
M|references|**Guarantee / Risk Reversal**
M|references|- Money-back guarantee
M|references|- Free trial terms
M|references|- "Cancel anytime"
M|references|- Reduces friction
M|references|**Stats Section**
M|references|- Key metrics that build credibility
M|references|- "10,000+ customers"
M|references|- "4.9/5 rating"
M|references|- "$2M saved for customers"
