M|references|1. Hero
M|references|2. Feature 1
M|references|3. Feature 2
M|references|4. Feature 3
M|references|5. Feature 4
M|references|6. CTA
M|references|```
M|references|This is a list, not a persuasive narrative.
M|references|```
M|references|1. Hero with clear value prop
M|references|2. soc proof bar (logos or stats)
M|references|3. Problem/pain section
M|references|4. How it works (3 steps)
M|references|5. Key benefits (2-3, not 10)
M|references|6. Testimonial
M|references|7. Use cases or personas
M|references|8. Comparison to alternatives
M|references|9. Case study snippet
M|references|10. FAQ
M|references|11. Final CTA with guarantee
M|references|```
M|references|This tells a story and addresses objections.
M|references|```
M|references|1. Hero (headline, subhead, CTA, image)
M|references|2. soc proof bar
M|references|3. 3 key benefits with icons
M|references|4. Testimonial
M|references|5. How it works (3 steps)
M|references|6. Final CTA with guarantee
M|references|```
M|references|Good for ad landing pages where brevity matters.
M|references|```
M|references|1. Hero (outcome-focused headline)
M|references|2. Logo bar (recognizable companies)
M|references|3. Problem section (business pain)
M|references|4. Solution overview
M|references|5. Use cases by role/department
M|references|6. sec/compliance section
M|references|7. Integration logos
M|references|8. Case study with metrics
M|references|9. ROI/value section
M|references|10. Contact/demo CTA
M|references|```
M|references|Addresses enterprise buyer concerns.
M|references|```
M|references|1. Hero with launch announcement
M|references|2. Video demo or walkthrough
M|references|3. Feature highlights (3-5)
M|references|4. Before/after comparison
M|references|5. Early testimonials
M|references|6. Launch pricing or early access offer
M|references|7. CTA with urgency
M|references|```
M|references|Good for ProductHunt, launches, or announcements.
M|references|Start with phrases like:
M|references|- "You know the feeling..."
M|references|- "If you're like most [role]..."
M|references|- "Every day, [audience] struggles with..."
M|references|- "We've all been there..."
M|references|Then describe:
M|references|- The specific frustration
M|references|- The time/money wasted
M|references|- The impact on their work/life
M|references|For each benefit, include:
M|references|- **Headline**: The outcome they get
M|references|- **Body**: How it works (1-2 sentences)
M|references|- **Proof**: Number, testimonial, or example (optional)
M|references|Each step should be:
M|references|- **Numbered**: Creates sense of progress
M|references|- **Simple verb**: "Connect," "Set up," "Get"
M|references|- **Outcome-oriented**: What they get from this step
M|references|Example:
M|references|1. Connect your tools (takes 2 minutes)
M|references|2. Set your preferences
M|references|3. Get automated reports every Monday
M|references|Best testimonials include:
M|references|- Specific results ("increased conversions by 32%")
M|references|- Before/after ctx ("We used to spend hours...")
M|references|- Role + company for credibility
M|references|- Something quotable and specific
M|references|Avoid testimonials that just say:
M|references|- "Great product!"
M|references|- "Love it!"
M|references|- "Easy to use!"